          <title>Eritrea's Biniam Girmay becomes the first Black African rider to win a Tour de France stage</title>
          <description><![CDATA[TURIN, Italy (AP) — Eritrean rider Biniam Girmay became the first Black African rider to win a Tour de France stage Monday when he sprinted to victory in the third stage. Girmay said his win was “for all Africans.” “We must be proud now. We are really part of the big races,” Girmay said.]]></description>
